# ASCII-Table widget is the easiest way to work with tables!

# Quick Guide

# 1. Press Ctrl + Enter (or Command + Enter on macOS) to execute the example below.
# 2. You can use either CIF or CFL notation.
# 3. To delete a column, rename it to "dd" or "Delete".
# 4. To plot a graph, append (x) and (y) to the column names, for example: "Column-1(x)".
# 5. To multiply a column by 2, append (*2) to its name, for example: "Column-1(*2)".
# 6. Popup window try to predict your input — use Tab to accept suggestion.

